  "title": "Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Established Marine Company recruiting Service Engineer/Technician :</strong></p><h2><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></h2><ul><li>You will be part of the Service Team, responsible for going onboard vessels to service, install, troubleshoot and commission marine communication and navigation equipment, as well as satellite equipment.</li><li>You would have to follow up with the customer’s requirements by liaising with the Service Manager and the technical support team to provide solutions for defects relating to marine equipment.</li><li>You are also required to prepare complete service reports upon conclusion of all jobs given.</li><li>On the job training will be provided for candidates who have no prior experience.</li><li>You may be required to travel overseas for service jobs from time to time.</li></ul><h2><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></h2><ul><li>Singaporeans or Singapore PRs are preferred</li><li>Candidates must possess at least a diploma in an engineering field.</li><li>Knowledge of Microsoft Word/Excel and IT Skills are required.</li><li>Must possess good communication, inter-personal and project management skills.</li><li>Must be able to travel overseas should the job requires.</li><li>There will be an added advantage for candidates with work experience in radar, autopilot, gyrocompass, satellite or other marine communication and navigation equipment.</li><li>Ex-marine related industries, ex-navy personnel will be considered. </li><li>Fresh graduates who are interested in the maritime industry are welcome to apply.</li></ul><p>Interested candidates please email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:career@cantrade.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">career@cantrade.com.sg</a> </p><p>To facilitate the recruitment process, please include your <u><strong>expected salary, last drawn salary, reason for leaving past employment and notice period</strong></u> in your resume.</p><p>We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be notified about their applications.</p>",
